-*- Mode: text -*-
mbackup for rsync.net online backup service
2009-10-07
Time-stamp: <2009-10-08>

Preparation before doing mbackup

1. get your account ready

2. add some alias/bookmarks
   ~/.ssh/config
   -------------
   Host rsync
     HostName usw-s008.rsync.net
     User 8368
     ForwardX11 no
     
   ~/.lftp/bookmarks
   -----------------
   rsync   sftp://8368@usw-s008.rsync.net

3. install your public key(s)
   #generate a authorized_keys file by concatenating
   #your public ssh key and root's public ssh key
   #upload it to authorized_keys file
   scp ~/keys/my-public-keys rsync:.ssh/authorized_keys
   #test your key is ready for every user:
   ssh rsync ls

Backup non-sensitive data using rsync.

Backup sensitive data:

first sign it with gpg, then upload using rsync.

